SIMPLE: intendment
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intendment
<hw>In*tend"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>entendement</ets> understanding, insight, F.
<ets>entendement</ets>, fr. LL. <ets>intendimentum</ets>. See
<er>Intend</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Charge; oversight.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Ford.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Intention; design; purpose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>intendment</qex> of God and nature.</q> <rj><qau>Jer.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The true meaning, understanding, or
intention of a law, or of any legal instrument.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intenerate</ent>⟦br⟧
